hpnicfTransceiver.name: hpnicfTransceiver

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

hpnicfTransceiver.description: The objects in this MIB module are used to display the information of transceiver on interface.

hpnicfTransceiverInfoTable.name: hpnicfTransceiverInfoTable
hpnicfTransceiverInfoTable.description: This table show the information of transceiver on interface.

hpnicfTransceiverHardwareType.name: hpnicfTransceiverHardwareType
hpnicfTransceiverHardwareType.description: Hardware type of the interface, such as SM(single mode).

hpnicfTransceiverType.name: hpnicfTransceiverType
hpnicfTransceiverType.description: Type of the interface, such as SFP/XFP/GBIC.

hpnicfTransceiverWaveLength.name: hpnicfTransceiverWaveLength
hpnicfTransceiverWaveLength.description: Wave length of the interface, measured in nanometer.

hpnicfTransceiverFiberDiameterType.name: hpnicfTransceiverFiberDiameterType
hpnicfTransceiverFiberDiameterType.description: The diameter of the fiber, measured in micron. fiber9 - 9 micron multi-mode fiber fiber50 - 50 micron multi-mode fiber fiber625 - 62.5 micron multi-mode fiber copper - copper cable.

hpnicfTransceiverTransferDistance.name: hpnicfTransceiverTransferDistance
hpnicfTransceiverTransferDistance.description: The maximal distance which the interface could transmit, measured in meter.

hpnicfTransceiverDiagnostic.name: hpnicfTransceiverDiagnostic
hpnicfTransceiverDiagnostic.description: Indicating the digital diagnostic monitoring function .

hpnicfTransceiverCurTXPower.name: hpnicfTransceiverCurTXPower
hpnicfTransceiverCurTXPower.description: Indicating the current transmitted power . The unit is in hundredths of dBM.

hpnicfTransceiverMaxTXPower.name: hpnicfTransceiverMaxTXPower
hpnicfTransceiverMaxTXPower.description: Indicating the maximal transmitted power . The unit is in hundredths of dBM.

hpnicfTransceiverMinTXPower.name: hpnicfTransceiverMinTXPower
hpnicfTransceiverMinTXPower.description: Indicating the minimal transmitted power . The unit is in hundredths of dBM.

hpnicfTransceiverCurRXPower.name: hpnicfTransceiverCurRXPower
hpnicfTransceiverCurRXPower.description: Indicating the current received power . The unit is in hundredths of dBM.

hpnicfTransceiverMaxRXPower.name: hpnicfTransceiverMaxRXPower
hpnicfTransceiverMaxRXPower.description: Indicating the maximal received power . The unit is in hundredths of dBM.

hpnicfTransceiverMinRXPower.name: hpnicfTransceiverMinRXPower
hpnicfTransceiverMinRXPower.description: Indicating the minimal received power . The unit is in hundredths of dBM.

hpnicfTransceiverTemperature.name: hpnicfTransceiverTemperature
hpnicfTransceiverTemperature.description: Indicating the current temperature. The unit is Celsius centigrade.

hpnicfTransceiverVoltage.name: hpnicfTransceiverVoltage
hpnicfTransceiverVoltage.description: Indicating the current voltage . The unit is in hundredths of V

hpnicfTransceiverBiasCurrent.name: hpnicfTransceiverBiasCurrent
hpnicfTransceiverBiasCurrent.description: Indicating the current bias electric current . The unit is in hundredths of mA

hpnicfTransceiverTempHiAlarm.name: hpnicfTransceiverTempHiAlarm
hpnicfTransceiverTempHiAlarm.description: Transceiver temperature high alarm threshold limit in thousandths of degrees Celsius. As an example: 49120 is 49.120 degrees Celsius.

hpnicfTransceiverTempLoAlarm.name: hpnicfTransceiverTempLoAlarm
hpnicfTransceiverTempLoAlarm.description: Transceiver temperature low alarm threshold limit in thousandths of degrees Celsius. As an example: 49120 is 49.120 degrees Celsius.

hpnicfTransceiverTempHiWarn.name: hpnicfTransceiverTempHiWarn
hpnicfTransceiverTempHiWarn.description: Transceiver temperature high warning threshold limit in thousandths of degrees Celsius. As an example: 49120 is 49.120 degrees Celsius.

hpnicfTransceiverTempLoWarn.name: hpnicfTransceiverTempLoWarn
hpnicfTransceiverTempLoWarn.description: Transceiver temperature low warning threshold limit in thousandths of degrees Celsius. As an example: 49120 is 49.120 degrees Celsius.

hpnicfTransceiverVccHiAlarm.name: hpnicfTransceiverVccHiAlarm
hpnicfTransceiverVccHiAlarm.description: Transceiver VCC high alarm threshold limit in hundreds of microvolts. As an example: 32928 is 3.2928 volts. Returns zero if not supported on the transceiver.

hpnicfTransceiverVccLoAlarm.name: hpnicfTransceiverVccLoAlarm
hpnicfTransceiverVccLoAlarm.description: Transceiver VCC low alarm threshold limit in hundreds of microvolts. As an example: 32928 is 3.2928 volts. Returns zero if not supported on the transceiver.

hpnicfTransceiverVccHiWarn.name: hpnicfTransceiverVccHiWarn
hpnicfTransceiverVccHiWarn.description: Transceiver VCC high warning threshold limit in hundreds of microvolts. As an example: 32928 is 3.2928 volts. Returns zero if not supported on the transceiver.

hpnicfTransceiverVccLoWarn.name: hpnicfTransceiverVccLoWarn
hpnicfTransceiverVccLoWarn.description: Transceiver VCC low warning threshold limit in hundreds of microvolts. As an example: 32928 is 3.2928 volts. Returns zero if not supported on the transceiver.

hpnicfTransceiverBiasHiAlarm.name: hpnicfTransceiverBiasHiAlarm
hpnicfTransceiverBiasHiAlarm.description: Transceiver bias high alarm threshold limit in microamps.

hpnicfTransceiverBiasLoAlarm.name: hpnicfTransceiverBiasLoAlarm
hpnicfTransceiverBiasLoAlarm.description: Transceiver bias low alarm threshold limit in microamps.

hpnicfTransceiverBiasHiWarn.name: hpnicfTransceiverBiasHiWarn
hpnicfTransceiverBiasHiWarn.description: Transceiver bias high warning threshold limit in microamps.

hpnicfTransceiverBiasLoWarn.name: hpnicfTransceiverBiasLoWarn
hpnicfTransceiverBiasLoWarn.description: Transceiver bias low warning threshold limit in microamps.

hpnicfTransceiverPwrOutHiAlarm.name: hpnicfTransceiverPwrOutHiAlarm
hpnicfTransceiverPwrOutHiAlarm.description: Transceiver transmit power high alarm threshold limit in tenths of microwatts. As an example: 10000 is 1 milliwatt.

hpnicfTransceiverPwrOutLoAlarm.name: hpnicfTransceiverPwrOutLoAlarm
hpnicfTransceiverPwrOutLoAlarm.description: Transceiver transmit power low alarm threshold limit in tenths of microwatts. As an example: 10000 is 1 milliwatt.

hpnicfTransceiverPwrOutHiWarn.name: hpnicfTransceiverPwrOutHiWarn
hpnicfTransceiverPwrOutHiWarn.description: Transceiver transmit power high warning threshold limit in tenths of microwatts As an example: 10000 is 1 milliwatt.

hpnicfTransceiverPwrOutLoWarn.name: hpnicfTransceiverPwrOutLoWarn
hpnicfTransceiverPwrOutLoWarn.description: Transceiver transmit power low warning threshold limit in tenths of microwatts. As an example: 10000 is 1 milliwatt.

hpnicfTransceiverRcvPwrHiAlarm.name: hpnicfTransceiverRcvPwrHiAlarm
hpnicfTransceiverRcvPwrHiAlarm.description: Transceiver receive power high alarm threshold limit in tenths of microwatts. As an example: 10000 is 1 milliwatt.

hpnicfTransceiverRcvPwrLoAlarm.name: hpnicfTransceiverRcvPwrLoAlarm
hpnicfTransceiverRcvPwrLoAlarm.description: Transceiver receive power low alarm threshold limit in tenths of microwatts. As an example: 10000 is 1 milliwatt.

hpnicfTransceiverRcvPwrHiWarn.name: hpnicfTransceiverRcvPwrHiWarn
hpnicfTransceiverRcvPwrHiWarn.description: Transceiver receive power high warning threshold limit in tenths of microwatts. As an example: 10000 is 1 milliwatt.

hpnicfTransceiverRcvPwrLoWarn.name: hpnicfTransceiverRcvPwrLoWarn
hpnicfTransceiverRcvPwrLoWarn.description: Transceiver receive power low warning threshold limit in tenths of microwatts. As an example: 10000 is 1 milliwatt.

hpnicfTransceiverErrors.name: hpnicfTransceiverErrors
hpnicfTransceiverErrors.description: Bitmask indicating transceiver errors. Transceiver information I/O error(0) Transceiver information checksum error(1) Transceiver type and port configuration mismatch(2) Transceiver type not supported by port hardware(3) WIS local fault(4) Receive optical power fault(5) PMA/PMD receiver local fault(6) PCS receive local fault(7) PHY XS receive local fault(8) Laser bias current fault(9) Laser temperature fault(10) Laser output power fault(11) TX fault(12) PMA/PMD transmitter local fault(13) PCS transmit local fault(14) PHY XS Transmit Local Fault(15) RX loss of signal(16) Unused(17-31)

hpnicfTransceiverChannelTable.name: hpnicfTransceiverChannelTable
hpnicfTransceiverChannelTable.description: This table provides statistics about transceiver with multi-channel.

hpnicfTransceiverChannelIndex.name: hpnicfTransceiverChannelIndex
hpnicfTransceiverChannelIndex.description: The channel index of transceiver. Indicating one channel of the interface.

hpnicfTransceiverChannelCurTXPower.name: hpnicfTransceiverChannelCurTXPower
hpnicfTransceiverChannelCurTXPower.description: Indicating the current transmission power. The unit is in hundredths of dBM.

hpnicfTransceiverChannelCurRXPower.name: hpnicfTransceiverChannelCurRXPower
hpnicfTransceiverChannelCurRXPower.description: Indicating the current received power. The unit is in hundredths of dBM.

hpnicfTransceiverChannelTemperature.name: hpnicfTransceiverChannelTemperature
hpnicfTransceiverChannelTemperature.description: Indicating the current temperature. The unit is Celsius centigrade.

hpnicfTransceiverChannelBiasCurrent.name: hpnicfTransceiverChannelBiasCurrent
hpnicfTransceiverChannelBiasCurrent.description: Indicating the current bias electric current. The unit is in hundredths of mA.
